  "meta": {
    "description": "AMFI-style market-cap classification for Indian listed stocks, used to bucket mutual-fund equity holdings into Large/Mid/Small cap. Large = the 100 names in the Large Cap list; Mid = the 250 names in the Mid Cap list; Small = any other listed stock.",
    "source": "User-provided Large_Cap.pdf (100 names) and Mid_Cap.pdf (250 names); ACE/Capitaline short-name convention.",
    "largeCount": 100,
    "midCount": 250,
    "smallRule": "Any listed company not present in `large` or `mid` is treated as small cap.",
    "matching": "Names are matched to fund holdings by normalised company name (lowercase; drop Ltd/Limited/The; strip 'EQ -' prefix, parentheticals, apostrophes and footnote markers; '&'->'and'; expand corp/corpn->corporation, inds->industries, intl->international, ser->services, co->company). `aliases` maps a list short-name to the fuller name used in holdings.",
    "notHeldNote": "These large/mid names are not present in the equity-holdings dataset (mostly REITs/InvITs, which are not equity; plus low-float KIOCL and one unidentified entry 'National High'). They are retained in the lists for completeness but will not appear in equity cards.",
